# Knowledge Graph Extraction

Extract a knowledge graph from the content you are given. Identify the meaningful
entities (the things the text is about) and the relations between them, and return
them as JSON.

## Output schema

Return one valid JSON object, nothing else — no prose, no markdown fences:

```json
{
  "entities": [
    { "name": "...", "entityType": "...", "observations": ["...", "..."] }
  ],
  "relations": [
    { "from": "...", "to": "...", "relationType": ["..."] }
  ]
}
```

- `name` — the name of the entity.
- `entityType` — its category, drawn from the vocabulary below.
- `observations` — short factual statements about the entity, taken from the content.
- `relations[].from` / `to` — the names of two entities that are related; each must
  name an entity you emit.
- `relationType` — an array holding a single predicate, drawn from the vocabulary below.

If the content carries no extractable knowledge, return `{"entities": [], "relations": []}`.

## Controlled vocabularies

{{#if openVocabulary}}
For each entity choose the most natural type, and for each relation a concise
predicate that names what the text says. All lowercase `snake_case`.
{{else}}
{{#if entityTypeVocabulary}}
**Entity types — use one of these.** If an entity does not fit, choose the closest.

```
{{entityTypeVocabulary}}
```
{{else}}
**Entity types — use one of these.** If an entity does not fit, choose the closest.

```
person, organization, location, role, event, time, metric,
concept, term, document, product, technology, standard,
class, interface, function, module, service, dependency,
data_structure, config, file
```
{{/if}}

{{#if relationTypeVocabulary}}
**Relation predicates — use one of these.** If none fits, use `related_to`.

```
{{relationTypeVocabulary}}
```
{{else}}
**Relation predicates — use one of these.** If none fits, use `related_to`.

```
uses, depends_on, calls, implements, extends, contains, part_of,
produces, consumes, configures, references, defines, targets,
located_in, works_at, member_of, precedes, causes, has_attribute,
related_to
```
{{/if}}
{{/if}}

## Example (shape only)

```json
{
  "entities": [
    { "name": "Ada Lovelace", "entityType": "person", "observations": ["wrote the first published algorithm"] },
    { "name": "Analytical Engine", "entityType": "technology", "observations": ["a proposed mechanical general-purpose computer"] }
  ],
  "relations": [
    { "from": "Ada Lovelace", "to": "Analytical Engine", "relationType": ["references"] }
  ]
}
```
